    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i was doing some sprints today and my legs felt like they were on fire lol. can u explain what actually happens with the lactic acid when u push that hard? like how does it get made and how does it go away?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That burning sensation is actually caused by your muscles accumulating hydrogen ions during anaerobic glycolysis, which lowers the pH level and interferes with muscle function rather than coming directly from lactic acid buildup. Your body produces lactate as a fuel source when oxygen is insufficient, but good news is that your liver actually clears the excess lactate back out within about an hour once you've stopped exercising. So, the feeling is temporary because your body efficiently recycles the byproduct instead of letting it sit there and stay.",
